# Nivoda Diamond Connector

This plugin integrates the Nivoda diamond API with WordPress and WooCommerce.

## Directory Structure

```
nivoda-diamond-connector/
├── nivoda-diamond-connector.php  # Main plugin file
├── includes/                      # PHP classes
│   ├── class-ndc-api.php         # API service wrapper
│   ├── class-ndc-cache.php       # Caching layer
│   ├── class-ndc-settings.php    # Admin settings
│   ├── class-ndc-cpt.php         # Custom post type
│   ├── class-ndc-ajax.php        # AJAX handlers
│   ├── class-ndc-woocommerce.php # WooCommerce integration
│   └── class-ndc-admin-tools.php # Admin tools
├── assets/                        # Frontend assets
│   ├── css/
│   │   ├── frontend.css          # Frontend styles
│   │   └── admin.css             # Admin styles
│   └── js/
│       ├── frontend.js           # Frontend JavaScript
│       └── admin.js              # Admin JavaScript
├── templates/                     # Template files
│   ├── search.php                # Search interface
│   └── single-diamond.php        # Single diamond view
├── languages/                     # Translation files
├── README.md                      # Documentation
└── readme.txt                     # WordPress.org readme
```

## Development

### Prerequisites

- WordPress development environment
- WooCommerce installed
- Nivoda API credentials

### Setup

1. Clone this repository to `wp-content/plugins/`
2. Activate the plugin in WordPress
3. Configure API settings

### Building for Production

No build step required - this is a pure PHP/JS plugin.

### Testing

1. Install and activate the plugin
2. Configure Nivoda API key in settings
3. Test API connection via admin tools
4. Add `[nivoda_search]` shortcode to a page
5. Verify search and filtering work correctly
6. Test add-to-cart functionality

